						content: { body: "\n            <p>\n              <a href=\"https://hiava.app/?utm_source=google&utm_medium=blog&utm_campaign=spotlight\">Ava</a> is an “AI-powered family operating system” designed to manage the logistics of family life by anticipating needs and automating tasks.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              The information parents manage is rarely structured; it arrives via inconsistent school emails, screenshots of flyers, PDF attachments, lengthy WhatsApp threads, and voice notes. Ava must understand the context and seamlessly interact with external services.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To handle the messy, unstructured inputs of the real world, the Ava team implemented a tiered architecture using <a href=\"https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models#gemini-2.5-flash\">Gemini 2.5 Flash models</a> for different stages of their agentic pipeline and the <a href=\"https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/live\">Live API</a> to provide a conversational interface.\n            </p>" }
