						type: "text",
						content: { body: "\n              <p>\n                Rooms empowers users to build and explore a universe of user-generated 3D experiences, much like a digital equivalent of LEGO. Available on the web and mobile, Rooms provides intuitive building tools and social features that foster creativity and connection. Hundreds of thousands of users are already creating, sharing, and playing in this vibrant digital world.\n              </p>\n              <p>\n                \"I have come to believe that creative expression isn't just a nicety, but rather a deep human need,\" says Jason Toff, the founder and CEO of Rooms. \"The internet is evolving to be richer and more immersive, which will necessitate 3D objects. The creation of these objects will be democratized, allowing anyone to build and share their creations. 3D objects will come to life and be interactive, further blurring the lines between the digital and physical worlds, and Gen AI is a key part of this evolution.\"\n              </p>\n              <p>\n                Rooms is now prototyping with Gemini 2.0 Flash to unlock a new era of avatar interaction, transforming static avatars into dynamic characters capable of engaging in rich, natural conversations:\n              </p>\n              <ul>\n                <li><p><strong>Dynamic conversations:</strong> Gemini 2.0 Flash's new audio out capabilities allow for more fluid and engaging conversations between avatars. Imagine avatars responding to user prompts not just with text, but with expressive, lifelike voices generated in real-time.</p></li>\n                <li><p><strong>AI-Powered personalities:</strong> Beyond dynamic conversations, Rooms is using Gemini 2.0 Flash to imbue each avatar with unique personality traits, backstories, and even motivations. By feeding Gemini 2.0 Flash rich character profiles and contextual information, Rooms can generate avatars that behave and interact in diverse and engaging ways. This opens up exciting possibilities for role-playing, collaborative storytelling, and emergent gameplay.</p></li>\n              </ul>" }
